<1ST_LINE>r i PM-UN-Peacekeeping     08-11 0709</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-UN-Peacekeeping,0774</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>U.N. Observer Group For Iran-Iraq Joins Six Others Currently At
Work</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Also in Thursday AMs report.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>UNITED NATIONS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United Nations is operating seven
peacekeeping and observer forces, including the just-formed
observer group to monitor the Iran-Iraq cease-fire.
   The forces are funded in a variety of ways. Some are included in
the regular U.N. budget; some are paid by special peacekeeping
assessments; and some receive voluntary contributions. The General
Assembly must authorize funding for major expenditures.
   Here is a look at the existing forces and their financing:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   NAME _ U.N. Iran-Iraq Military Observer Group.
   CREATED _ Aug. 9, 1988.
   LOCATION _ Iran-Iraq border war front region.
   HEADQUARTERS _ Not yet established. Iran and Iraq are to provide
necessary offices and facilities.
   MISSION _ To observe cease-fire to take effect Aug. 20, monitor
Iraqi and Iranian troops withdrawals to their own countries, and
assist the implementation of U.N. Security Council Resolution 598,
which also calls for an exchange of prisoners of war.
   PARTICIPATING COUNTRIES _ Argentina, Australia, Austria,
Bangladesh, Canada, Denmark, Finland, Ghana, Hungary, Indonesia,
India, Ireland, Italy, Kenya, Malaysia, New Zealand, Nigeria,
Norway, Poland, Senegal, Sweden, Turkey, Yugoslavia, and Zambia.
   STRENGTH _ 350 observers.
   FINANCING _ The group is expected to cost $74 million over a
six-month period. The means of funding is still being worked out.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   NAME _ U.N. Good Offices Mission in Afghanistan and Pakistan.
   CREATED _ April 14, 1988.
   LOCATION _ Afghanistan.
   HEADQUARTERS _ Kabul, Afghanistan, and Islamabad, Pakistan.
   MISSION _ To monitor Soviet troop withdrawal from Afghanistan,
which is to be complete by Feb. 15, 1989.
   PARTICIPATING COUNTRIES _ The observers were dispatched from
other existing U.N. peacekeeping and military observation groups.
   APPROXIMATE STRENGTH _ 50.
   FINANCING _ The Afghanistan observer force does not have a
separate budget, and may dissolve in February when all Soviet
troops are to be out of Afghanistan.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   NAME _ U.N. Disengagement Observer Force.
   CREATED _ June 3, 1974.
   LOCATION _ Syrian Golan Heights.
   HEADQUARTERS _ Damascus, Syria.
   MISSION _ To supervise cease-fire between Israel and Syria after
the 1974 Middle East war.
   PARTICIPATING COUNTRIES _ Austria, Canada, Finland, Poland.
   APPROXIMATE STRENGTH _ 1,330.
   FINANCING _ The United Nations has assessed its 159 members
about $35 million for the 1988 expenses of the U.N. Disengagement
Observer Force and its subsidiary Arab-Israeli peacekeeping
operations, payable to the U.N.'s special peacekeeping budget.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   NAME _ U.N. Interim Force in Lebanon.
   CREATED _ March 19, 1978.
   LOCATION _ Southern Lebanon.
   HEADQUARTERS _ Naqoura, Lebanon.
   MISSION _ To confirm Israeli withdrawal from Lebanon after the
Israeli invasion, and to ensure peace and security in the area.
   PARTICIPATING COUNTRIES _ Fiji, Finland, France, Ghana, Ireland,
Italy, Nepal, Norway, Sweden, United States.
   APPROXIMATE STRENGTH _ 5,800.
   FINANCING _ The force is budgeted at about $140 million a year.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   NAME _ U.N. Truce Supervision Organization.
   CREATED _ June 11, 1948.
   LOCATION _ Beirut and the Sinai.
   HEADQUARTERS _ Jerusalem.
   MISSION _ various Arab-Israeli truce missions; assists observer
forces in Syria and Lebanon.
   PARTICIPATING COUNTRIES _ Argentina, Australia, Austria, Canada,
Chile, Denmark, Finland, France, Ireland, Italty, Netherlands, New
Zealand, Norway, Sweden, Soviet Union, United States.
   APPROXIMATE STRENGTH _ 295.
   FINANCING _ UNTSO was estimated to cost $41.5 million in the
1988-89 budget. The funds come from the regular U.N. operating
budget.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   NAME _ U.N. Military Observer Group In India and Pakistan.
   CREATED _ Jan. 24, 1949.
   LOCATION _ India-Pakistan border areas.
   HEADQUARTERS _ Rawalpindi, Pakistan and Srinagar, India.
   MISSION _ To supervise India-Pakistan cease-fire in
Jammu-Kashmir area.
   PARTICIPATING COUNTRIES _ Australia, Chile, Denmark, Finland,
Italy, New Zealand, Norway, Sweden, Uruguay, United States.
   APPROXIMATE STRENGTH _ 36.
   FINANCING _ This group also gets its funds from the regular
budget. The world body budgeted almost $7.3 million for its 1988-89
activities.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   NAME _ U.N. Peacekeeping Force in Cyprus.
   CREATED _ March 27, 1964.
   LOCATION _ Cyprus.
   HEADQUARTERS _ Nicosia.
   MISSION _ Maintaining buffer between Greek and Turkish regions
of Cyprus.
   PARTICIPATING COUNTRIES _ Australia, Austria, Canada, Denmark,
Finland, Ireland, Sweden, United Kingdom.
   APPROXIMATE STRENGTH _ 2,100.
   FINANCING _ The Cyprus force receives its funds through appeals
to U.N. members, about half of which provide contributions. The
secretary-general has estimated its 1988 operating costs at more
than $25 million.
</TEXT>
