<HEAD>Tropical Storm Beryl Starts To Break Up; Thunderstorms Heavy In
Some Areas</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Tropical storm Beryl was breaking up as it moved slowly across
northeast Texas today after leaving up to an inch of rain in
southeast Texas and western Louisiana.
   Intense thunderstorms developed in eastern North Dakota and
western Minnesota on Wednesday night, producing high winds, hail
and brief heavy rains.
   Winds gusted to 60 mph near Hillsboro, N.D., and to 65 mph at
Ada, Minn. Golf ball-sized hail fell near Mayville, N.D., while
hail and nearly an inch of rain fell on Harwood, N.D.
   Other showers and thunderstorms were scattered over southwest
Texas, New Mexico, Montana, Florida and along the Atlantic Coast
from Georgia to New Jersey.
   The high in the nation Wednesday was 112 degrees at Lake Havasu
City, Ariz., and Borrego Springs, Calif.
   Today's weather forecast called for showers and thunderstorms in
the lower Mississippi Valley, the eastern two-thirds of the Gulf
Coast, Florida, the southern Atlantic Coast, and parts of Texas and
the Appalachians.
   Because of the vestiges of tropical storm Beryl, thunderstorms
were predicted to be most numerous over central Arkansas. Numerous
thunderstorms also were expected in southern Florida.
   Forecasters said showers and thunderstorms should be scattered
in parts of the mountain regions of Arizona and New Mexico, and
southwest Texas; thunderstorms should develop later in the day from
the northern Plains to the northern Mississippi Valley.
   The rest of the nation should have mostly sunny skies, and highs
in the 90s were predicted for most of the country.
   Readings in the 80s were forecast from the northern Atlantic
Coast to the upper Great Lakes states; in the 70s and 80s over the
Pacific Northwest and along the California coast; near 100 in
southwest and south-central Texas and the northern Plains; and
100-110 in the desert Southwest and California valleys.
   The nation's temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 49 degrees
at Yellowstone, Wyo., to 95 at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 73 foggy; Boston 77 cloudy; Buffalo 66 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 77 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 71 hazy; Cleveland 73
foggy; Miami 78 cloudy; New York 76 partly cloudy; Philadelphia 77
