<2ND_LINE>PM-Dead Horse,0236</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Horse Dragged From Pickup Truck</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMPTONVILLE, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man in a pickup truck dragged a dead
horse on a rope four miles, smearing a country road with entrails,
the sheriff says.
   ``This whole community is very, very upset about it,'' said
Yadkin County Sheriff Jack Henderson. ``And I can understand why.''
   Henderson said he would investigate. No charges were filed.
   Dean Cole told authorities that the horse had died of colic at
his house and that he tied the carcass to the back of his truck and
dragged it to a relative's farm Tuesday to be buried, Henderson
said.
   ``He freely admits to doing it _ and also admits he made a
mistake doing it,'' the sheriff said.
   Julie Goodin, director of the Forsyth County Humane Society,
questioned Cole's account, and some residents accused him of
dragging the horse to its death.
   ``It was alive when I saw it go up the road,'' said Frieda Hall.
``It was trotting, but even a trot is too fast for an animal in
this heat.''
   She said she saw entrails scattered about the road. ``It was
just everywhere,'' she said. ``It was so much I figured it must
have fallen off some truck.''
   Ms. Goodin said the humane society received two complaints. ``I
just think this is really sad,'' she said.
</TEXT>
