<1ST_LINE>r a PM-FatalFall     08-11 0224</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Fatal Fall,0229</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Killed In Fall From Amusement Park Ride</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man died of head injuries today after
falling 15 feet from a whirling amusement park ride, police said.
   Witnesses reported that the man appeared to be clowning around
and was not secured by the safety bar Wednesday night, said Bill
Ramsey, a Peony Park spokesman.
   Byron James Conant, 31, of Missouri Valley, Iowa, died at
Methodist Hospital after the fall from the Hurricane, which has six
two-seat cars extended on arms that rotate and move up and down
about a center shaft.
   Police Sgt. Mike Cavanaugh said Conant was in the front seat of
a car with a friend in the back. He said the operator noticed
Conant in an unsafe position about 20 seconds into the ride but was
unable to stop the ride before the man fell.
   Witnesses told officers Conant appeared to be kneeling outside a
safety bar or turning around to talk to his friend, Cavanaugh said.
He said the bar appeared to be operating properly, but he ordered
the ride closed for further investigation.
   Ramsey said the park has operated the Hurricane for several
years without accident. The last serious accident at the park
occurred about 12 years ago when a person died on a ride that later
was removed, he said.
