<HEAD>Man Arrested After Slugging Police Horse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was saddled with a night in jail for
punching a police officer's horse in the face, police said.
   Officers Claude S. Hall and Thomas A. Hall said they were
patrolling near headquarters Wednesday when they saw 52-year-old
Alvaro Hernandez littering.
   The officers said they tried to talk to the man, but he became
angry and slugged Hall's horse, then grabbed the reins and shoved
the horse and Hall into the street, police said. Neither the
officer nor the horse fell.
   The horse was not seriously hurt.
   Hernandez was jailed on $413 bail Wednesday on charges of
reckless conduct and littering.
