<HEAD>Daughter Watches As Woman Shot To Death While Waiting At Traffic
Light</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman fatally shot a 32-year-old woman in
the head as she waited in a car with her 8-year-old daughter for a
traffic light to change, and police said they had no motive for the
slaying.
   Dorothea Hutchinson, a cosmetology student, was shot Tuesday in
an unincorporated area south of downtown, sheriff's Deputy Dan Cox
said. The gunman fled before authorities arrived.
   The girl was not harmed.
   The car rolled into a fence after the shooting, and Ms.
Hutchinson's daughter Kristen jumped out of the car and ran to a
home for help, said Hertesene McDowell, Ms. Hutchinson's mother.
   ``She asked the people to call paramedics, and she then called
me,'' Ms. McDowell said. ``When I arrived, she asked me: `Granny,
did I do the right thing? My mother always told me to do that if
anything ever happened to her.'''
   Ms. Hutchinson was rushed to Martin Luther King Jr.-Drew Medical
Center where she died early Wednesday, said Walter Gray, assistant
hospital administrator.
   Police said they had not determined a motive and no suspects
were in custody early Thursday.
