<TEXT>
   Sen. Bob Dole's request not to have his name
put in nomination for the presidency at the Republican National
Convention may mean he's a top candidate as the party's vice
presidential nominee, Kansas Republicans said Thursday.
   Party officials also said Dole's decision is a sign he wants to
promote party unity for Vice President George Bush, who is assured
of receiving the presidential nomination next week.
   State GOP Chairman Fred Logan Jr. announced Dole's decision not
