<TEXT>
   Inspectors are spot-checking New Orleans'
1,615 taxi drivers for price gouging, faulty meters and other
mechanical problems in anticipation of next week's Republican
National Convention.
   The spot-checks will continue through the GOP convention and
beyond, said Byron Woods, administrator of the New Orleans Taxicab
Bureau.
