<HEAD>London Shares Drop Sharply After Early Gains</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices surrendered their early gains and
fell sharply by midday Thursday on renewed jitters about the course
of global interest rates and prospects for overseas markets.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 10.2
points, or 0.6 percent to 1,829.7 at about 12:30 p.m.
   The index moved in positive territory for most of the morning,
rising as much as 6.3 points.
   Volume was moderate at 270.3 million shares compared with 239.6
million shares at the same time Wednesday.
   Shares traded higher at the outset of business, helped by a
rally in Tokyo stocks earlier Thursday and gains in U.S. bond
prices during Japanese trading.
