<1ST_LINE>d f PM-HaworthAcquires     08-11 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Haworth Acquires,0166</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Office Furniture Manufacturer Buys European Seating Company</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Dollars are U.S.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>HOLLAND, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Furniture manufacturer Haworth Inc. has
purchased a European-based seating company for nearly $30 million,
Haworth officials announced today.
   Haworth, one of the world's largest manufacturers of office
systems furniture, acquired the Comforto Group from Vickers Public
Limited Co., a $1.5-billion British holding company known for
producing Rolls Royces and the world's first military tanks.
   A Vickers spokesman said the transaction was a cash deal for
$29.5 million.
   Comforto, based in Ahlen, West Germany, produces office chairs
and conference tables as well as seating for conference rooms and
auditoriums. The company has 500 employees worldwide and had sales
of about $50 million last year.
   Haworth, with 2,800 employees worldwide, had sales of about $400
million last year, the Holland-based company said.
   Comforto's European and U.S. operations will operate as
subsidiaries of Haworth and will continue under current management,
Haworth officials said.
</TEXT>
