<1ST_LINE>r f BC-AutoProdn     08-11 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Prodn,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
167,983 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
145,939, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's projected production is higher than the same week a
year ago, in which 149,102 cars and light trucks were produced, the
trade journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 98,658 cars this week,
compared with 82,853 a week ago and 83,993 in the same week in 1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 69,325,
compared with last week's 63,086 and last year's 65,109.
   Canadian automakers were to build 14,023 cars this week, up from
6,162 a week ago and from last year's 3,729.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 12,476,
compared with 8,253 a week ago and 12,703 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
